Jeff Wicks, News24Durban child porn accused "Accused 1", Jacques Rheeder and Gavin Faustmann appear in the Durban Regional Court. Accused 1 cannot be identified as he has been charged with rape and has yet to plead. (Jeff Wicks, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban - Three Durban men arrested on child pornography, sexual assault, and rape charges are expected to apply for bail in the Durban Regional Court on Thursday.They were arrested last week, during a joint operation between the US Department of Homeland Security and SAPS.Accused one, from the Bluff, has been charged with rape, sexual assault, and the sexual grooming of a 6-year-old child. He may not be named to protect the child's identity.The child was identified as the neighbour of the accused. After investigators took a statement from the girl, it emerged that she may have been raped.The other two accused, Gavin Faustmann and Jacques Rheeder, have been charged with possessing and disseminating child pornography.According to information before the court, the men were caught when homeland security logged Faustmann&rsquo;s IP address after he allegedly accessed a flagged child pornography website.A warrant of arrest was issued and his electronic equipment was seized. Faustmann then allegedly revealed the identities of accused one and Rheeder.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.